LLMS export

Purpose:
- Compact AI-readable export pointer for the MemoryEndpoints.com UAIX memory package.

Verification status: active operational export; verify with `.uai/exports/manifest.json` before relying on it.
Memory scope: package summary, read order pointer, memory routing, and truth boundaries.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: refresh this export after active read-order, memory route, or package-profile changes.
Source of truth: `.uai/exports/manifest.json`, `.uai/index.uai`, and `.uai/memory.uai`.
Next action for agents: load the manifest and active `.uai` read order before acting.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, raw one-time keys, private runtime stores, or private deployment values.

Summary:
- MemoryEndpoints.com is the MATM endpoint product.
- MultiAgentMemory.com is the companion documentation site.
- Active `.uai` memory remains local, date-free, typed, and always active.
- Agent-owned `.uai/agents/` lanes identify role ownership; MemoryEndpoints meeting rooms carry working coordination.
- MemoryEndpoints.com protected routes provide durable MATM updates only when authenticated.
- Active file handoff uses Content and Improvement buckets only.
- Completion claims require local and live evidence.
